repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of correspondence, memoranda, minutes, financial reports, pamphlets and press clippings documenting the activities and operations of the Association of Yale Alumni (AYA).

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 8-C (YRG 8-C), Records of organizations of Yale alumni

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: While this collection as a whole is available for research, parts of it may be restricted due to law, university policy or fragility. Any restricted material will be noted as such.

Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Association of Yale Alumni Records (RU 792). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged as follows: I. Society of the Alumni, 1826-1911. II. Commencement Registers, 1842-1911. III. Committee for Plan on University Development, 1917-1921. IV. University Alumni Fund Association, 1875-1961. V. Reunions, 1902-1968. VI. Alumni Board, 1939-1964. VII. Founding Board of Governors of the Association of Yale Alumni, 1971-1975. VIII. Association of Yale Alumni, 1972-1977; and in subseuqent accessions

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of correspondence, memoranda, minutes, financial reports, pamphlets and press clippings documenting the activities and operations of the Association of Yale Alumni (AYA)
